Title: On Non-Abelian Thomas-Fermi Screening
Authors: G. Alexanian and V.P. Nair (Physics Dept., CCNY)
Comments: 7 pages, plain Tex, no figures; one reference added, note added at
  the end
Report-no: CCNY-HEP 96/10
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B390 (1997) 370-374
\\
  The Thomas-Fermi screening of non-Abelian gauge fields by fermions or
screening of gluon fields in quark matter is discussed. It is described by an
effective mass term which is, as with hard thermal loops, related to the
eikonal for a Chern-Simons theory and the Wess-Zumino-Witten action.
